// SOURCE: Source Files/Intergrations/Fusion Intergrations 2/ReactorCLI/Product Guide.txt
// NOTE: Integrated into the Fusion FSN tree for migration traceability.
// CONTENT:
// Product Guide: ReactorCLI1. ArchitectureReactorCLI is built on three pillars:The Parser: A high-performance string tokenizer.The Resolver: A layered state machine that queries CLI args, Env vars, and Config files.The Prompter: An abstraction layer over crossterm/ratatui that renders TUI elements.2. Design PrinciplesProgressive Disclosure: Simple usage is simple. Complex distributed features are opt-in.Zero-Panic: Parsing failures should lead to helpful prompts, not stack traces.Type Safety: All arguments are strongly typed. Enum variants render as selectable TUI lists.3. Roadmapv1.0: TUI Fallback, Env/Config resolution.v1.1: "Telepathic" Tab Completion (fetches live data from cluster for autocomplete).v2.0: Voice Input integration (WebAudio -> WASM -> ReactorCLI).
